</CENTER><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Lanys Community Forum</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Shaman</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Strategy Advice</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://acinternet.com/lanys/newTopic.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; &nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic><IMG SRC=http://acinternet.com/lanys/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showMessage?topicID=16.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showMessage?topicID=10.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%"><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#10226A><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#10226A><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ureptilicus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reptilicus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8/3/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8:07:14 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Strategy Advice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm trying to kick around a few strategies for soloing my way through 35. While kiting mobs in the Overthere last night, my fellow guild Shaman stumbled across an amazing discovery: Remember level 1? Well that level 1 Flash of Light spell works rather well for soloing tactics (until you finally get a new blindness spell 38 levels later <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). It causes a brief (very brief 5 - 12 secs) fear effect. But for only 12 mana, I could easily cast this 20 times, spending less mana than 2 nukes, and keep the mob running back and forth well my wolf tanks him. So strategy so far would be pull with Malisement, root, stack all 3 decent DoTs (evenomed breath, scourge, and affliction, yes scourge and affliction DO stack together), send in pet, and then keep blinding. I figure that is WAY more mana efficient than root, dot, nuke, nuke, root, nuke, med. If anyone has used this, or a similar strategy, as sort of a poor man's reverse-kiting, please give me some info. </font><P><h4><font color="#880066">Reptilicus Maximus - Order of the Ebon Tear<h4> <i><font color="#002211">Level 35 Iksar Shaman<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulelleashawindsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lelleasha Windsong</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8/3/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>9:53:14 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Strategy Advice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">ahhhhhh very much more mojo efficent Rep, I only have my DD mem'ed when theres a chanter or other caster in our group and then only use it to pull something off them.  <br>
<br>
Normally when I solo, I togor, sick poochie, VOS, Scourge (depending on the number of hps the mob has) and jump in, VOS again if it wears off before the mob is done, and remember to not let the poochie do more then 50% damage cause he will take half of your ex and with a hell level this is something you dont want to do.<br>
<br>
Another fun thing I tried with the birds in SK was to slow, stack dots, root and sit and med and watch the bird stew <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  this was pre pooch </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubranispiritblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brani SpiritBlood</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8/11/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8:41:05 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Strategy Advice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Maybe your root works better than mine, but the nasty little birdies and gnollies kept breaking mine, smacking me around while I was medding, and generally just disturbing the whole process of mana gain.<br>
<br>
To avoid that, I'd med up/ cann down, put a fresh sow and regn on, dot, dot and run the gnollie in the general direction of the birdhouse, stopping long enough to re-poison him when it wore off. About the time I'd get to the birdhouse, I'd turn around and melee (GASP) him down, as he was running away. Repeat process for aviak avocet or harrier, this time bringing him to paw. Gave me a change of scenery, and broke up the boredom that way</font><P><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#330033">B</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#660066">ra</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990099">ni</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4"> 
  <font color="#CC00CC">Sp</font><font color="#FF00FF">ir</font><font color="#CC00CC">it</font><font color="#990099">Bl</font><font color="#660066">oo</font><font color="#330033">d</font><br>
  <font size="2" color="#660066">Resident ShayBabe Extraordinaire</font></font><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukragar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kragar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8/11/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>10:36:49 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Strategy Advice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hmm, I'm currently soloing Giants at the Burning Woods Zone in Frontier Mountains.  My strategy is:  1)  Pull with Togors to Pet (/pet guard here), Root at Pet, Scourge, VoS, Cannibalize, med a bit, jump up and tank him down).  If its a Giant Craig I'll need 2 VoS, heheh.<br>
<br>
It works pretty well, especially if you have quickness on the pet.</font><P><b><font size="5" face="chiller">Kragar Frostburn - <font size="5" face="chiller" color=red>Lone Wolf</font><br>
<font size="5" face="chiller" color=blue>Tribunal Shaman of 41 Winters</font><br>
<a href=http://www.lanys.com><font size="5" face="chiller" color=green>Lanys T'vyl</font></a><br><font size="5" face="chiller">a kewl dewd_00 says "sow plz Jabekn!"</b></font><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ureptilicus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reptilicus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8/11/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11:42:59 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Strategy Advice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Heh, yeah I've also been soloing mountain giants in FM. There's a BIG difference between soloing them and soloing Forest Giants <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  As the MG's hit for in the 80's and the FG Evergreens (the toughest ones) hit for about 60 if I remember correctly. My Flash of Light theory was just not that well thought out. They still start running at full speed, and that can be deadly in FM, all you need is for them to pick up a Goblin Bonecharmer or a Burynai Cenobite, and they'll make a wallet out of me, when I'm solo<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I haven't found my Dot, dot, dot, root, med, re-root when needed strategy to be too effective on them, as they break root about every 10 secs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and Enstill is just worthless! I just usually spend more time running and rooting than I do medding <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> To any Shaman below level 34, I would not recommend buying Enstill.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> So I've found that if I want to kite, I'll just group with a ranger, necro, or druid and get a good movement reducing spell at my hands <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , or just Root, send pet, dot, dot, nuke, nuke, nuke, root, nuke, med (or similar strategy). Hehe, just my 2cp. </font><P><font color=blue><B>Reptilicus Maximus</b></font></br><b><i>Iksar Shaman</b></i><br><br><font color=blue><B>Canof</b></font></br><b><i>Iksar Warrior</b></i><br><h3><font color=blue><b><i>Order of the Ebon Tear<P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showMessage?topicID=16.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showMessage?topicID=10.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=4><IMG SRC=http://acinternet.com/lanys/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.emailToFriend?topicID=14.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.threadControl?topicID=14.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshaman.subs